U.S. Stocks Extend Drop as S&P Says It May Cut Ratings on EU, Europe Banks

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-12-07T19:49:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/u-s-stocks-extend-drop-as-s-p-says-it-may-cut-ratings-on-eu-europe-banks.html
U.S. stocks extended losses after
 Standard & Poor’s  said it may cut the European Union’s credit
rating as well as ratings on BNP Paribas SA, Commerzbank AG and
Deutsche Bank AG.  The S&P 500 slipped 0.4 percent to 1,253.81 at 2:46 p.m. in
 New York .  The EU had its AAA long-term rating put on “creditwatch
negative” by S&P Ratings Services after a similar action on 15
of the 17 Euro members. The EU’s short-term A-1+ rating was
affirmed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  